Definitely buy it if your looking for a slightly more typical though good JRPG but if your just buying it it because you liked the previous Chaos Rings you should consider this more carefully.

The Game is a Mobile RPG Masterpiece.  1) Story: From the get go, you get the sense that the story is on a grand scale with plenty of depth and lovable characters. From start to finish of the main quest took me about 26 hours (not including all the sidequests, after game content,  and the arena mode). The whole thing has a Phantasy Star Online feeling to it, but with its own unique style and charisma, that really impressed me  2) Gameplay: The battle system is well fleshed-out and very enjoyable. I like the way that you are not timed to take your moves, unlike many Final Fantasy titles. Another strength of the game is that you have great control over its difficulty, and later, even obtaining choice over whether or not you encounter basic enemies. At the same time Boss Battles still keep their same levels regardless of what skill level you choose at the start of a quest, so you still get that feeling of progress and keeping the game at reasonable difficulty. Controls are easy and intuitive, if just a tad finicky in the camera department.  3) Presentation: From the engaging fully orchestrated music scores, to the 3D Character and equipment models, to the voice acting, and well animated cutscenes, this game looks and feels console a quality experience in the palm of your hand. Sure there are games with better graphics out there, but the art style in Chaos Rings 3 is still delightful to look at and never got in the way of myself taking the experience seriously.  4) Final Thoughts: Chaos Rings 3, for even a mild RPG fan, is worth every penny in my opinion. The story, gameplay, and presentation are all quite engaging, and to use book terminology, I would say its definitely a "page turner." The production definitely felt high budget and gave a fully-fledged RPG on an epic scale, to mobile gaming. My only complaint is that the ending felt rather abrupt and left me seriously wanting for a sequel. All in all, this game is a worthy addition to any mobile gamer's library, especially those who enjoy a good rpg. Here's to hoping that mobile gaming receives more beautiful, engaging, quality titles such as this one!  9/10

Chaos Rings III is a console quality jrpg on your phone. $20 might seem a lot but it's well worth it and many would buy this game for $40 if it was on the 3DS or PS vita.  It has a good story,  amazing Music  and good characters that all seem to have a believable goal other than just save the world.   The things I did not like was that it gets very very grindy late game, the  game was going to be F2P before they changed their mind to premium. This is apparent by the in game premium coins that give you access to special items.   You now get these premium coins by doing in game quests but it takes a long time to get enough to buy the good items (Unless you cheat with your calender)   This game is a great game filled with charm and awesome music thats held back buy the F2Pishness of grindiness late game. Still worth $20, but just be prepared  8/10

Ok so heres the (Sort of easter eggish) backstory SE isn't telling you that Im seeing from my playthrough so far. The setting is Far future, Marble blue is actually our own planet earth, and has apparently been over run by monsters, and probably went through some crazy end of the world scenario. The north pole appears to have become scarred with fire and lava. Humans no longer inhabit earth, but live in a bio dome space station thingy and liscenced explorers are sent to earth on various quests.

Hint: Since there is no cloud save you can copy the save files over to a new Android phone if you want to move your saved progress to a new phone. ||aesthetic 5*,gameplay 5*,execution 5*,ovarall 5*||  Great sense of humor through whole game! Very close to Final Fantasy X vibe (still not there, but Media Vision can't hide their roots). Well written, but a little generic and overgrinding daily quest, with many links to previous games/characters. Some may complain that artstyle is a bit off, especially in comparison with previous in the serie, but is truly good. Finally, battle mechanics evolved into the perfect balance between fast paced action and turn base fights. 10 out of 10 Pigtapirs recommends this game! Even the Patty can...my pigtapir called Patty! :) worthy 25 bucks. Took half year to bring this game to the global market!? Square, want more my money? Put ChR 3 OST on Google play. If anyone has problem with not-responding buttons, turn your tablet 180 degree :). Fan of the serie here. ||XperimentD 15.3.2015 Galaxy S I9000 Dell Venue 7||
